featured_reviews.review_id: The staff are very friendly and helpful. The room we were in was spotless and spacious good AC and ceiling fan, decor was classical same as the hotel. Which has undergone major transformation. Food very good however they served our soup and main course at the same time, so had to have the main dish taken back and kept hot till we were ready for it. All in all the hotel is well fit for purpose but it's location is a bit off-putting. We also found the drinks prices were a lot higher than we had expected but again all hotels will be in a similar situation. External noise was also louder than we would have chosen, no soundproofing. Room furniture was classical and very nice and comfortable. Streets to hotel are quite narrow so a short walk is required, staff kindly come and take your luggage to and from the hotel and deliver to your room. Steps into hotel are steep with no wheelchair access.

featured_reviews.review_id:
Excellent hotel. This hotel has preserved its ethnicity and roots very well. The rooms are lovely and have the luxury feel.
The staff are amazing they go above and beyond. The service is excellent.
Upon arrival you are very nicely greeted the hospitality is top class here.
Food was very good quality and really tasty. There is always someone to greet you and help you.
You can do kite flying. Chill on the terrace. During dinner times they have beautiful Indian music or dancing which really to the great ethnic atmosphere to the hotel. Great location in Chandni Chowk, easy to access shops and rickshaws.
We are a young couple travelling and I would stay here and again and recommend to my friends and family.

Warmth and Hospitality Personified
The staff at Haveli Dharampura truly made my stay exceptional. Their welcoming smiles and genuine care made me feel like a cherished guest. From the reception to the dining area, their impeccable service added an extra layer of comfort and joy to my experience.

featured_reviews.review_id:
I am a bit conflicted about this place. The building itself is absolutely beautiful. The renovation was well carried out. Nevertheless, the rooms are really tiny and face inside the court. Therefore, there isn't much natural sunlight inside the room unless you open the curtains to everybody walking inside the courtyard.
It is definitely quite pricey. It's really up to someone if he can justifies the price.
